        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/larry_link/{size}/1312_2.png",
        "created_at": "2022-05-01T21:53:32.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Agreed on the 11 Coche Meursault, my tasting note from a year ago. This was from a bottle of the Domaine et Selection Meursault, farmed and vinified by Coche.</p>\n<p>3/31/2021 rated 92 points: Popped and poured. The nose is singing, flint, white flowers, and lemon rind. The palate is deep with a lovely viscosity. Lemon and spice flavors, high acidity and cut, with a lingering finish. This is just beautiful and in the perfect spot tonight paired with a classic risotto dish from Venice flavored with peas and prosciutto.</p>",
